Mrs Gitanjali was admitted with above mentioned history. She was
admitted in ICU and underwent urgent hemodialysis after insertion of
right femoral HD catheter, In view of deranged renal functions, anuric
state, hyperkalemia with ECG changes. She underwent NCCT KUB which
was s/o new soft tissue lesions, suggestive of progressive disease by
RECIST criteria, bladder outlet obstruction and b/I Hydronephrosis. She
underwent foleys catherisation, post which she passed good amount of
urine. USG screening post foleys catherisation showed improvement in
Hydronephrosis. Urology and interventional radiology review was done
and advised to continue with medical / conservative management and

follow up for need of PCN.
Patient and family was counselled in detail regarding disease, prognosis
and plan of management in detail, also regarding need to follow up for
PCN, if needed.
Pain management team review was done for back pain, advise was
followed. Medical oncology review was done, and was advised to follow
up OFD.
She received 2 unit LDPRC for hb stablisation and 1 session of dialysis
during hospital stay.
Now she is being discharged with following advise.

Observations: HRCT CHEST Right hilar node measures 40mm
vs 10mm. Nodule is seen in right middle lobe measuring 11mm
(SAD) (new finding) There is bilateral pleural effusion & smooth
septal thickening & mild pericardial effusion. Rest unchanged.
CT KUB Note is made of a soft tissue thickening in the bladder
base 7 vaginal vault region, which seems to be deviated
towards left side. It measures 4.8x4.7cm (AP x TR) vs
4.8x3.2cm. There is moderate ascites with omental fat
stranding. (New finding) No identifiable hepatic, renal, adrenal,
peripancreatic lesion. Both kidneys are moderately
hydronephrotic with mild parenchymal thinning of left kidney.
Right kidney measures 12.4cm. Left kidney measures 10.4cm.
There is an enlarged right inguinal lymph nodes with AP
diameter of 16mm. (New finding) Small bowel not dilated.
Urinary bladder is grossly distended. Rest unchanged.
IMPRESSION: Follow up case of Ca cervix, post op, post RT
with wall recurrence. . Comparison with previous PET CT dated
25-08-2020, there is appearance of new soft tissue lesions,
suggestive of progressive disease by RECIST criteria . There is
evidence of bladder outlet obstruction with bilateral
hydronephrosis accompanied by fluid retention in pleural,
pericardial & peritoneal space.
Condition at Discharge
